# Production Environment Variables Template

Copy this to Railway and Vercel dashboard respectively.

## For Railway (Backend)

```
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/database
# Get this from Railway PostgreSQL service Variables tab

# Session & Auth
SESSION_SECRET=generate-a-random-long-string-at-least-32-chars-12345678901234567890
REPL_ID=railway-prod

# API Configuration
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=5000
ISSUER_URL=https://replit.com/oidc

# Frontend URL (for CORS if needed)
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-vercel-domain.vercel.app
```

## For Vercel (Frontend)

```
# API Endpoint - point to your Railway backend
VITE_API_URL=https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app
```

---

## How to Generate SESSION_SECRET

Run this in your terminal:

```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

Use the output for SESSION_SECRET.

---

## Getting Your URLs

### Railway Backend URL
1. Open your Railway project
2. Go to your backend service
3. Click the **Share** or **Public URL** button
4. Copy the URL (looks like: `https://polished-prompt-prod.up.railway.app`)

### Vercel Frontend URL
1. After deploying to Vercel
2. Your URL will be shown on the dashboard
3. Usually: `https://your-project.vercel.app`

---

## Important Security Notes

⚠️ **NEVER commit `.env` files with real secrets**
⚠️ **Use different SESSION_SECRET for production**
⚠️ **Keep DATABASE_URL private**
⚠️ **Use unique, strong secrets - not example values**

